PRD: CopyCanto — The Ultimate Voice Cloning & Singing App
Version: 1.1 (March 2026)
Status: BUILD-READY (Post-Red Team Audit)
Target Platform: Web (Optimized for macOS / M1 Max Local Execution)

SECTION 1: EXECUTIVE OVERVIEW
1.1 — Product Vision Statement
CopyCanto is a professional-grade, locally-hosted singing voice conversion suite. It empowers creators to clone any voice with high fidelity (RVC v2) or instant zero-shot speed (kNN-SVC), and seamlessly apply those clones to existing songs or YouTube tracks through high-precision stem separation (Demucs v4).

1.2 — Success Metrics & KPIs
| Category | Metric | Target (MVP) | Measurement Method |
|---|---|---|---|
| Quality | Fidelity Score | >= 9.0/10 | Internal blind A/B testing |
| Stability | OOM Crash Rate | 0% | Error log monitoring (Sequential Guard) |
| Speed | Conversion Time | < 30s (kNN) | Backend execution logs |

SECTION 2: FEASIBILITY SPIKES
2.1 — Spike Identification
SPIKE 1: Sequential Metal (MPS) Orchestrator
	•	RISK: Concurrent execution of Demucs and RVC will crash the M1 Max 32GB.
	•	TEST: A Rust-based Mutex guard that prevents Process B from starting until Process A returns Exit Code 0.
	•	SUCCESS: Memory peaks at <24GB during heavy workloads.

SPIKE 2: RVC v2 Metal (MPS) Inference
	•	RISK: RVC is optimized for CUDA; Metal support can be unstable.
	•	TEST: Execute a 3-minute conversion using --device mps and verify output audio integrity.
	•	SUCCESS: Inference completes in < 1x realtime (3 mins audio in < 3 mins).

SPIKE 3: YouTube-to-Demucs File Handoff (NEW)
	•	RISK: yt-dlp file permissions and naming conventions may break the Demucs input path.
	•	TEST: Download a video -> extract audio -> move to stems/ -> trigger Demucs via a single automated script.
	•	SUCCESS: Automated pipeline produces isolated stems from a URL with zero manual file moving.

