SECTION 6: API REGISTRY & WIRING
6.1 — API Endpoint Registry (The Backend Contract)
| Method | Path | Description | Payload Schema |
|---|---|---|---|
| GET | /api/jobs/active | Check for running processes | — |
| POST | /api/create/start | Initiate the sequential pipeline | { engine, voice_id, source_type, source_url } |
| GET | /api/voices | Fetch all voice clones | — |
| POST | /api/voices/train | Start RVC training job | { name, audio_file, avatar_file } |
| GET | /api/songs | Fetch all processed stems | — |
| GET | /api/covers | Fetch final generated covers | — |
| DELETE | /api/covers/{id} | Remove a cover and local file | — |

6.2 — Cross-Feature Wiring Matrix
| Feature | Target | Handoff Trigger | Data Passed |
|---|---|---|---|
| Processing | Cover Lib | JOB_COMPLETE WS | cover_id, file_path |
| YouTube Extractor | Song Lib | EXTRACTION_DONE Event | song_id, stem_paths |
| Voice Trainer | Voice Lib | TRAIN_DONE Event | model_path, voice_id |

SECTION 7: TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE
7.1 — Asset Storage Protocol (M1 Max Sandbox)
To bypass browser restrictions, the backend serves files via a Local Assets Proxy:
	•	Path: http://localhost:8888/assets/{type}/{filename}
	•	All library images and audio files are accessed via this internal URL.

7.2 — Gemini API Features (Orchestrator)
Feature: YouTube Metadata Cleaning
	•	Model: Gemini 2.5 Flash
	•	System Prompt: "You are a music metadata specialist. Given a YouTube video title, return a clean JSON object with 'artist' and 'song_title'. Remove fluff like '[Official Video]', '(HD)', or artist channel suffixes."

7.3 — Google Stitch Instructions
	•	Design Tokens: Use Apple-Glass-Dark and Apple-Glass-Light.
	•	Transitions: Every screen transition must use a 100ms fade-in/out to mimic macOS Monterey.
	•	Navigation: Buttons must use the liquid-hover animation class.

