SECTION 9: ANTIGRAVITY ROADMAP & OPEN SOURCE ENGINES
9.1 — Engine Integration Strategy
CopyCanto is designed as a modular shell for state-of-the-art open source audio engines. The following engines are referenced in the codebase and slated for full integration:

1. RVC v2 (Retrieval-based Voice Conversion)
   - Role: Primary singing voice conversion engine.
   - Repo: https://github.com/RVC-Project/Retrieval-based-Voice-Conversion-WebUI
   - Integration: Python-based inference script (`engines/process.py`) called via Node.js `child_process`.
   - Status: Ready for MPS (Metal) optimization.

2. kNN-SVC (k-Nearest Neighbors Singing Voice Conversion)
   - Role: Instant, zero-shot voice cloning.
   - Repo: https://github.com/asdfghjkl/knn-svc
   - Integration: Lightweight inference pipeline for rapid prototyping.
   - Status: Roadmap Q2 2026.

3. Demucs v4 (Hybrid Transformer Stem Separation)
   - Role: Source material isolation.
   - Repo: https://github.com/facebookresearch/demucs
   - Integration: Pre-processing step for all YouTube and local uploads.
   - Status: Active pipeline component.

9.2 — Local LLM Orchestration (Ollama)
Instead of cloud-based Gemini orchestration, CopyCanto uses a local LLM via Ollama for metadata cleaning and job orchestration.
- Endpoint: `http://localhost:11434/api/generate`
- Model: `llama3` or `mistral` (Configurable in Settings)
- System Prompt: "You are a music metadata specialist. Given a YouTube video title, return a clean JSON object with 'artist' and 'song_title'. Remove fluff like '[Official Video]', '(HD)', or artist channel suffixes."

9.3 — Antigravity Handoff Protocol
To ensure seamless takeover by Antigravity, the following architectural standards are maintained:
- Firebase as Source of Truth: All job states, metadata, and user preferences are synced via Firestore.
- Sequential Mutex: Backend logic ensures only one heavy GPU/MPS task runs at a time to prevent OOM.
- Standardized File Paths: All assets are stored in a predictable `/assets/{type}/{id}` structure.
- API-First Design: The frontend communicates exclusively via the documented REST API, allowing the backend to be swapped or scaled independently.
